{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/seanmonstar/reqwest/issues/1897","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/seanmonstar/reqwest","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/seanmonstar/reqwest/issues/1897/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/seanmonstar/reqwest/issues/1897/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/seanmonstar/reqwest/issues/1897/events","html_url":"https://github.com/seanmonstar/reqwest/issues/1897","id":1789348555,"node_id":"I_kwDOA7dkLM5qp0rL","number":1897,"title":"BOM in `Response::text_with_charset`","user":{"login":"ollyswanson","id":42551149,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQyNTUxMTQ5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/42551149?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ollyswanson","html_url":"https://github.com/ollyswanson","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ollyswanson/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ollyswanson/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ollyswanson/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ollyswanson/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ollyswanson/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ollyswanson/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ollyswanson/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ollyswanson/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ollyswanson/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":1283983666,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxMjgzOTgzNjY2","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/seanmonstar/reqwest/labels/E-pr-welcome","name":"E-pr-welcome","color":"c2e0c6","default":false,"description":"The feature is welcome to be added, instruction should be found in the issue."}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":5,"created_at":"2023-07-05T11:23:49Z","updated_at":"2023-07-06T16:32:20Z","closed_at":"2023-07-06T16:32:20Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Hi, just seeking a bit of clarification on whether including the byte order mark in decoded UTF-8 is intentional or not when calling `Reponse::text` & `Response::text_with_charset`.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n        let (text, _, _) = encoding.decode(&full);\r\n        if let Cow::Owned(s) = text {\r\n            return Ok(s);\r\n        }\r\n        unsafe {\r\n            // decoding returned Cow::Borrowed, meaning these bytes\r\n            // are already valid utf8\r\n            Ok(String::from_utf8_unchecked(full.to_vec()))\r\n        }\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nBy ignoring the `Cow::Borrowed` branch we're returning `full` which can include a BOM, whereas the str slice in the `Cow::Borrowed` returned by the call to `decode` strips the BOM.\r\n\r\nThis tripped us up when trying to deserialize an XML response after calling `.text()` and I'm unclear on where the responsibility for removing the BOM should live.\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"seanmonstar","id":51479,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUxNDc5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/51479?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar","html_url":"https://github.com/seanmonstar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmon